parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the accelerator pedal is difficult to depress
the vehicle accelerates while in reverse gear
the cruise control sticks and accelerates without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to jerk or pull to one side, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or pulls to one side when braking
the steering wheel jerks hard to one side
loss of control of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and blowout can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
Cracks on the tire sidewall can lead to air loss, causing loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: tire damage that cannot be repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire vibration and dimpling can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: dimples or indentations on the tire sidewall

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving.
